                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>From July 20 to July 24 representatives of the United Kingdom, led by Lord
                    Tedder, Marshal of the Royal Air Force, and Sir Oliver Franks, Ambassador in the
                    United States, met at Washington with representatives of the United States, led
                    by General Omar Bradley, Chairman of the Joint Chiefs of Staff, and Philip C.
                    Jessup, Ambassador at Large, to discuss the world situation. Iran was among the
                    issues discussed with both sides agreeing that they “should insofar as possible
                    assist the Iranian Government to strengthen its position” and that “an overt
                    Soviet attack on Iran would raise an immediate question of general war.” For
                    further documentation on these meetings, including the summary of the
                    discussions quoted from above, see <ref target="frus1950v03#pg_1654">volume III,
                        pages 1654</ref> ff.</p>
            </div>
